Reality TV Star, Pere Egbi has reacted to reports that the popular TV show, BBNaija form is for sale. DAILY POST had reported that organisers of the show, on Sunday announced auditions for season 7 of the show. A post on its verified Twitter page, said that auditioning for the show would commence from 15th May 2022 to 30th May 2022. Interested participants were asked to log on to AfricaMagic.tv/bbaudtion, upload a 3-minute video introducing themselves, what is unique about them, their likes and dislikes and why they should be chosen this season. Speaking on the auditions, Pere on his Instagram page clarified that the form was not for sale. He urged Nigerians to stop asking him how much the form is. He wrote: “Please BBNaija Auditions are free. No come dey ask me how much to buy form. “